[[File:Brno CZ Crypt at the Capuchin Monastery 01.jpg|thumb|The crypt]]
The '''Capuchin Crypt in Brno''' is a funeral room mainly for [[Capuchin]] friars. The crypt was founded in the mid 17th century in the basement of the Capuchin Monastery in the historical centre of [[Brno]].<ref name="monastery">{{Cite web|url=http://www.kapucini.cz/index.php?option=com_content&view=article&id=10:capcrypt&catid=7:englishbrno&Itemid=11|title=Capuchin Crypt|publisher=The Capuchin Monastery in Brno|accessdate=6 October 2011|language=English}}</ref> The bodies of people buried there turned into [[mummies]] because of the geological composition of the ground and the system of airing.<ref name="monastery"/>

